"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Quantums and Subticks\\n\\n\\nIn dYdX, quantities and prices are represented in quantums (for quantities) and subticks (for prices), which need conversion for practical understanding.\\n\\n## Quantums\\n\\nThe smallest increment of position size. Determined from `atomicResolution`.\\n\\natomicResolution - Determines the size of a quantum. [For example](https://github.com/dydxprotocol/v4-testnets/blob/aa1c7ac589d6699124942a66c2362acad2e6f50d/dydx-testnet-4/genesis.json#L5776), an `atomicResolution` of -10 for `BTC`, means that 1 quantum is `1e-10` `BTC`.\\n\\n## Subticks\\n\\nHuman-readable units: `USDC/<currency>` e.g. USDC/BTC\\n\\nUnits in V4 protocol: `quote quantums/base quantums` e.g. (`1e-14 USDC/1e-10 BTC`)\\n\\nDetermined by `quantum_conversion_exponent`, this allows for flexibility in the case that an asset’s prices plummet, since prices are represent in subticks, decreasing `subticks_per_tick` would allow for ticks to denote smaller increments between prices.\\n\\nE.g. 1 `subtick` = `1e-14 USDC/1e-10 BTC` and if BTC was at 20,000 USDC/BTC, a `tick` being 100 USDC/BTC (`subtick_per_tick` = 10000) may make sense.\\n\\nIf BTC drops to 200 USDC/BTC, a `tick` being 100 USDC/BTC no longer makes sense, and we may want a `tick` to be 1 USDC/BTC, which lets us set `subtick_per_tick` to 100 to get to a `tick` size of 1 USDC/BTC.\\n\\n## Interpreting block data\\n\\n![Interpret1](/interpret_block_data_1.png)\\n\\n\\n::::steps\\n### Buy or Sell\\nFirst, notice row I is negative. That means this trade is a sell by the taker account. If It was positive, it would be a buy.\\n\\n\\n### Market determination\\nNext, look at row N. The perpetual_id is 7, which maps to AVAX-USD market. You can see all the mappings from this endpoint for the dYdX Chain deployment by dYdX Operations Services Ltd. https://indexer.dydx.trade/v4/perpetualMarkets where the clobPairId is the perpetual_id.\\n\\n### Quantity determination\\nNext, we need to get the decimals for this market. First, get the atomicResolution from that endpoint above which we see is -7. Now we can get the size of the trade. From row I and J, take this number -500000000 and multiply by 10^(AtomicResolution) and you get: -500000000 x 10^-7 = 50, so the quantity is 50.\\n\\n### Price determination\\nNext, look at row, E, F, G, H, I, and J\\n\\n![Interpret2](/interpret_block_data_2.png)\\n\\nThe price of the trade is either `abs((G+E)/I)*10e(-6 - AtomicResolution)`, or `abs((H+F)/J)*10e(-6 - AtomicResolution)`, either one is the same. Note that the ‘-6’ is because the AtomicResolution of USDC is -6.\\n\\n`abs((1479130125 + 369875)/-500000000)*10e(-6 + 7) = 29.59`\\n\\n`abs((-1479337255 - 162745)/500000000)*10e(-6 +7) = 29.59`\\n\\n### Conclusion\\nIn conclusion, we have determined that this trade is SELL 50 AVAX-USD at price $29.59\\n\\n::::\\n\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#quantums-and-subticks\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>In dYdX, quantities and prices are represented in quantums (for quantities) and subticks (for prices), which need conversion for practical understanding.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#quantums-and-subticks\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nIn dYdX, quantities and prices are represented in quantums (for quantities) and subticks (for prices), which need conversion for practical understanding.\\n\",\"title\":\"Quantums and Subticks\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#quantums\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The smallest increment of position size. Determined from <code>atomicResolution</code>.</p>\\n<p>atomicResolution - Determines the size of a quantum. <a href=\\\"https://github.com/dydxprotocol/v4-testnets/blob/aa1c7ac589d6699124942a66c2362acad2e6f50d/dydx-testnet-4/genesis.json#L5776\\\">For example</a>, an <code>atomicResolution</code> of -10 for <code>BTC</code>, means that 1 quantum is <code>1e-10</code> <code>BTC</code>.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#quantums\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe smallest increment of position size. Determined from atomicResolution.\\natomicResolution - Determines the size of a quantum. For example, an atomicResolution of -10 for BTC, means that 1 quantum is 1e-10 BTC.\\n\",\"title\":\"Quantums\",\"titles\":[\"Quantums and Subticks\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#subticks\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Human-readable units: <code>USDC/&lt;currency&gt;</code> e.g. USDC/BTC</p>\\n<p>Units in V4 protocol: <code>quote quantums/base quantums</code> e.g. (<code>1e-14 USDC/1e-10 BTC</code>)</p>\\n<p>Determined by <code>quantum_conversion_exponent</code>, this allows for flexibility in the case that an asset’s prices plummet, since prices are represent in subticks, decreasing <code>subticks_per_tick</code> would allow for ticks to denote smaller increments between prices.</p>\\n<p>E.g. 1 <code>subtick</code> = <code>1e-14 USDC/1e-10 BTC</code> and if BTC was at 20,000 USDC/BTC, a <code>tick</code> being 100 USDC/BTC (<code>subtick_per_tick</code> = 10000) may make sense.</p>\\n<p>If BTC drops to 200 USDC/BTC, a <code>tick</code> being 100 USDC/BTC no longer makes sense, and we may want a <code>tick</code> to be 1 USDC/BTC, which lets us set <code>subtick_per_tick</code> to 100 to get to a <code>tick</code> size of 1 USDC/BTC.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#subticks\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nHuman-readable units: USDC/&lt;currency&gt; e.g. USDC/BTC\\nUnits in V4 protocol: quote quantums/base quantums e.g. (1e-14 USDC/1e-10 BTC)\\nDetermined by quantum_conversion_exponent, this allows for flexibility in the case that an asset’s prices plummet, since prices are represent in subticks, decreasing subticks_per_tick would allow for ticks to denote smaller increments between prices.\\nE.g. 1 subtick = 1e-14 USDC/1e-10 BTC and if BTC was at 20,000 USDC/BTC, a tick being 100 USDC/BTC (subtick_per_tick = 10000) may make sense.\\nIf BTC drops to 200 USDC/BTC, a tick being 100 USDC/BTC no longer makes sense, and we may want a tick to be 1 USDC/BTC, which lets us set subtick_per_tick to 100 to get to a tick size of 1 USDC/BTC.\\n\",\"title\":\"Subticks\",\"titles\":[\"Quantums and Subticks\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#interpreting-block-data\",\"html\":\"\\n<p><img src=\\\"/interpret_block_data_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"Interpret1\\\"/></p>\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"3\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#interpreting-block-data\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Interpreting block data\",\"titles\":[\"Quantums and Subticks\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#buy-or-sell\",\"html\":\"<p>First, notice row I is negative. That means this trade is a sell by the taker account. If It was positive, it would be a buy.</p></div><div data-depth=\\\"3\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#buy-or-sell\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"First, notice row I is negative. That means this trade is a sell by the taker account. If It was positive, it would be a buy.\",\"title\":\"Buy or Sell\",\"titles\":[\"Quantums and Subticks\",\"Interpreting block data\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#market-determination\",\"html\":\"<p>Next, look at row N. The perpetual_id is 7, which maps to AVAX-USD market. You can see all the mappings from this endpoint for the dYdX Chain deployment by dYdX Operations Services Ltd. <a href=\\\"https://indexer.dydx.trade/v4/perpetualMarkets\\\">https://indexer.dydx.trade/v4/perpetualMarkets</a> where the clobPairId is the perpetual_id.</p></div><div data-depth=\\\"3\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#market-determination\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Next, look at row N. The perpetual_id is 7, which maps to AVAX-USD market. You can see all the mappings from this endpoint for the dYdX Chain deployment by dYdX Operations Services Ltd. https://indexer.dydx.trade/v4/perpetualMarkets where the clobPairId is the perpetual_id.\",\"title\":\"Market determination\",\"titles\":[\"Quantums and Subticks\",\"Interpreting block data\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#quantity-determination\",\"html\":\"<p>Next, we need to get the decimals for this market. First, get the atomicResolution from that endpoint above which we see is -7. Now we can get the size of the trade. From row I and J, take this number -500000000 and multiply by 10^(AtomicResolution) and you get: -500000000 x 10^-7 = 50, so the quantity is 50.</p></div><div data-depth=\\\"3\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#quantity-determination\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Next, we need to get the decimals for this market. First, get the atomicResolution from that endpoint above which we see is -7. Now we can get the size of the trade. From row I and J, take this number -500000000 and multiply by 10^(AtomicResolution) and you get: -500000000 x 10^-7 = 50, so the quantity is 50.\",\"title\":\"Quantity determination\",\"titles\":[\"Quantums and Subticks\",\"Interpreting block data\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#price-determination\",\"html\":\"<p>Next, look at row, E, F, G, H, I, and J</p><p><img src=\\\"/interpret_block_data_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"Interpret2\\\"/></p><p>The price of the trade is either <code>abs((G+E)/I)*10e(-6 - AtomicResolution)</code>, or <code>abs((H+F)/J)*10e(-6 - AtomicResolution)</code>, either one is the same. Note that the ‘-6’ is because the AtomicResolution of USDC is -6.</p><p><code>abs((1479130125 + 369875)/-500000000)*10e(-6 + 7) = 29.59</code></p><p><code>abs((-1479337255 - 162745)/500000000)*10e(-6 +7) = 29.59</code></p></div><div data-depth=\\\"3\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#price-determination\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Next, look at row, E, F, G, H, I, and JThe price of the trade is either abs((G+E)/I)*10e(-6 - AtomicResolution), or abs((H+F)/J)*10e(-6 - AtomicResolution), either one is the same. Note that the ‘-6’ is because the AtomicResolution of USDC is -6.abs((1479130125 + 369875)/-500000000)*10e(-6 + 7) = 29.59abs((-1479337255 - 162745)/500000000)*10e(-6 +7) = 29.59\",\"title\":\"Price determination\",\"titles\":[\"Quantums and Subticks\",\"Interpreting block data\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/quantums#conclusion\",\"html\":\"<p>In conclusion, we have determined that this trade is SELL 50 AVAX-USD at price $29.59</p></div></div>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/quantums.mdx#conclusion\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"In conclusion, we have determined that this trade is SELL 50 AVAX-USD at price $29.59\",\"title\":\"Conclusion\",\"titles\":[\"Quantums and Subticks\",\"Interpreting block data\"]}]}}"
